articles.description: Thousands of Israelis took to the streets on Saturday demanding that Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's government do more to secure the release of hostages being held in the Gaza Strip by Islamist group Hamas.
articles.title: Protesters return to streets across Israel, demanding hostage release

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Five people were killed and nine wounded in three separate Ukrainian drone and artillery strikes on the Russian border provinces of Belgorod and Kursk, and the city of Donetsk, which Russia claims to have annexed, local officials said on Saturday.
articles.title: Five killed in Ukrainian strikes on Russian border regions, Donetsk, officials say

articles.description: A regional poll on Sunday offers Catalans the choice of an exiled separatist politician or an anti-independence government.
articles.title: Catalans vote in election that offers new chance to exiled separatist leader

articles.title: About 50,000 march against foreign agent bill in Tbilisi, Georgia

articles.author: Jacob Gronholt-Pedersen
articles.description: Dutch contestant Joost Klein has been expelled from Saturday's Eurovision Song Contest final after a complaint by a member of the production crew, organisers said, adding to the headaches for host Sweden as it also grapples with anti-Israel protests.
articles.title: Joost Klein expelled as Eurovision braces for protests

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: An overnight drone attack launched from Ukraine sparked a brief fire at an oil refinery in the Volgograd region in southern Russia, the region's governor said on Sunday.
articles.title: Ukraine-launched drone sparks fire at Russia's Volgograd refinery, regional governor says

articles.author: Andrius Sytas
articles.description: Lithuanians vote on Sunday in a presidential election expected to hand a new term to incumbent Gitanas Nauseda, a staunch supporter of Ukraine in its two-year war with Russia, following a campaign focusing on security concerns in the Baltic states.
articles.title: Lithuanian presidential hopefuls vow to stand up to Russian threat

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Philippines said on Saturday it has deployed ships to a disputed area in the South China Sea, where it accused China of building "an artificial island" in an escalating maritime row.
articles.title: Philippines sends ships to disputed atoll where China building 'artificial island'
